+Add the ability for tasks to declare dependencies on other tasks, so they only become available once their prerequisites are done.
 
 ## Requirements
 
-- A task with dependencies remains blocked (not available for dequeue) until ALL dependencies have `completed` status
-- When a dependency completes (via `complete(taskId)`), the system checks if any dependent tasks are now unblocked
-- Circular dependencies must be detected and throw an error at enqueue time
-  - Direct circular: A depends on B, B depends on A
-  - Indirect circular: A → B → C → A
-- `getDependencies(taskId)` returns an array of `{ taskId, status }` objects
-- Dependency on a non-existent task ID should throw an error
-- A failed dependency does NOT auto-fail the dependent task - it stays blocked
-- Cascading dependencies work: if A depends on B and B depends on C, A is only available after both B and C complete
+- When adding a task, you can specify a list of task IDs that must complete before this task becomes available.
+- A task with unresolved dependencies is blocked and will not be returned when retrieving.
+- When a dependency completes, the system should check whether any blocked tasks are now unblocked.
+- Circular dependencies (direct or indirect) must be detected and rejected at task-creation time.
+- Depending on a non-existent task should cause an error.
